# RTS Engine Implementation Plan

> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.

**Goal:** Build a modular low-poly 3D RTS engine (Warcraft 3 style) that renders terrain and animated models with an RTS camera, supporting both WC3 formats (.mdx/.blp) and standard formats (glTF/PNG/JPG).

**Architecture:** Modular static libraries (core, platform, renderer, assets, terrain, camera) consumed by an editor executable. Each module exposes abstract interfaces for swappability. Communication between modules via a pub/sub EventBus.

**Tech Stack:** C++17, OpenGL 3.3, GLFW 3.4 (Wayland), CMake, Conan 2.x, Google Test, ImGui, spdlog, glm, stb, tinygltf, glad, Doxygen + Sphinx/Breathe.

**Spec:** `docs/superpowers/specs/2026-03-27-rts-engine-design.md`

